= Welcome to Blerb!

== Installation
  * Install merb-core, merb-more and merb-plugins from wycats repo on github
  
  * Install merb-core
    * git clone git://github.com/wycats/merb-core.git
    * cd merb-core
    * rake install
    * sudo cp bin/merb /usr/bin/merb
    
  * Install merb-more
    * git clone git://github.com/wycats/merb-more.git
    * cd merb-more
    * rake install
    * cd merb-more/merb-action-args
    * rake install
    * cd merb-more/merb-assets
    * rake install
    
  * Install merb-plugins
    * git clone git://github.com/wycats/merb-plugins.git
    * cd merb-plugins/merb_datamapper
    * rake install
    * cd merb-plugins/merb_helpers
    * rake install
    
  * git clone git://github.com/hornbeck/blerb-core.git - anon checkout
  * git clone git@github.com:hornbeck/blerb-core.git   - commit access
  * cd blerb-core
  * mv config/database.yml.sample config/database.yml
  * fill in the correct database credentials
  * rake dm:db:automigrate
    * automigrate seems to be broken at the moment.  A better bet is to import the blerb.sql file from config
  * script/blerb

Blerb should now be running on port 4000, so open up your browser and visit localhost:4000!

== Dependencies (versions tested)


merb-core         (0.9)
merb_helpers      (0.9)
merb_datamapper   (0.9)
merb-mailer       (0.9.1)
merb-assets       (0.9.0)
merb-action-args  (0.9.0)
datamapper        (0.3.0)
rspec             (1.1.3)
merb_stories      (0.1.0)

